					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1956625&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610224927" alt="DrChandra" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1956625)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;" >DrChandra</a></span> <span class="odate time_1542962987 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Nov 2018 08:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4065751">
									

<p>Understandable, and in all fairness to you this may just be somewhat clunky exposition on my part, however I would like to point out that 'all her secrets' is an overstatement. She just says 'I programmed this myself using Chaos Runes' and that her phone is flagging his texts as memetic malware, which isn't all that much, and since dado has already hacked her phone he knows at least that much already. She doesn't say anything compromising that he doesn't already know.</p>
<p>And at that point, she's not so much disturbed as irritated. She's still underestimating dado, and does not regard it as 'crisis situation', just a nuisance. She's not rattled until the text where she says she's rattled. She's competent, but not infallible, and here at least dado is in the incarnation of obfusticating stupidity.</p>
<p><strong>Edit:</strong> Come to think of it, dado gives away his origin story without cause, and that's much more compromising. Foolish, foolish dado.</p>

							</div>

								
